# Benjamin Riesser, MPA

**Benjamin Riesser, MPA**, is a data scientist and institutional performance analyst with 13+ years of experience helping organizations make better decisions with their data. He combines deep technical skill in statistical analysis, data governance, and pipeline development with a public affairs background and proven experience advising senior leaders, federal agencies, and cross-functional teams. His track record spans designing measurement systems, stewarding data quality, administering analytical platforms, and translating complex findings into clear guidance for non-technical decision-makers. He is a recent federal contractor (Public Trust) with prior U.S. Navy service.

Key accomplishments include: architected Snowflake data pipelines integrating multi-source government datasets (improved data accessibility and processing efficiency); developed CQI reporting systems delivering performance insights to the Administration for Children and Families (ACF); automated quality improvement reporting using RMarkdown, streamlining production of hundreds of customized agency reports; and designed operational auditing programs assessing treatment model fidelity across 25+ provider agencies (reduced compliance gaps and triggered targeted corrective action).

